trips.title: Gods Own Country
trips.description: Kerala is a beautiful state in the southwest of India, often called “God’s Own Country” because of its lush greenery, serene backwaters, and rich culture. 🌴
highlights: Backwaters & Houseboats: Alleppey and Kumarakom are famous for peaceful houseboat cruises.  Hill Stations: Munnar and Wayanad are known for tea plantations
and Marari have scenic beaches with golden sand.  Wildlife: Periyar and Wayanad wildlife sanctuaries offer trekking and wildlife spotting.  Culture & Food: Traditional Kathakali dance

trips.title: Visit Dubai
trips.description: Dubai is one of the most iconic place in the world,known for its luxury, modern architecture,and cultural diversity.
highlights: Burj Khalifa – the world’s tallest building with breathtaking views from the observation deck.  Dubai Mall & Mall of the Emirates – world-class shopping
and entertainment under one roof.  Palm Jumeirah & Atlantis – man-made island resorts and beaches.  Desert Safari – dune bashing
and traditional Bedouin-style dinners.  Dubai Creek & Souks – explore gold
and textile markets to feel the old Dubai charm.  Luxury Experiences – skydiving over the Palm

trips.title: Maldives
trips.description: The Maldives is a tropical island nation in the Indian Ocean, southwest of India and Sri Lanka. It consists of about 1,200 coral islands grouped into 26 natural atolls. Known for its white-sand beaches, turquoise lagoons, and vibrant coral reefs, it’s one of the world’s most sought-after holiday destinations.
highlights: 🏝️ Stay in an overwater villa with breathtaking ocean views  🤿 Snorkel or dive in vibrant coral reefs full of marine life  🌅 Sunset dolphin cruise across the turquoise waters  🍽️ Private sandbank picnic or beach candlelight dinner  🧘 Relax with spa treatments and yoga by the sea  🚤 Explore local islands and Maldivian culture  🏄 Enjoy water sports like kayaking
